---
import MarketingPageLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingPageLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingPageLayout
  title="Gameye Platform: Provider-agnostic game server orchestration"
  description="Explore the Gameye platform architecture for region-aware orchestration, observability, and cost-aware multiplayer scaling."
  canonical="https://gameye.com/platform/"
  ogType="website"
  ogImage="https://gameye.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/gameye_architecture_white.png"
  ogImageAlt="Gameye platform architecture diagram"
  schemaType="WebPage"
  schemaName="Gameye Platform"
>
  <section class="section page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="subtitle">Platform</p>
      <h1>Provider-agnostic orchestration built for multiplayer at scale.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Deploy and operate game sessions across cloud and bare metal providers through one control layer, one API,
        and one operational workflow.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/contact-us/">Talk to sales</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/how-it-works/">See how it works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container cards">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Global placement control</h3>
        <p>Route sessions to optimal regions with policy-driven provider selection and latency-aware orchestration.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Operational observability</h3>
        <p>Monitor fleet state, labels, and lifecycle behavior with real-time operational context for live teams.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Cost-aware scaling</h3>
        <p>Scale capacity by demand while balancing provider mix and infrastructure cost in one deployment model.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container split">
      <div>
        <p class="subtitle">Architecture</p>
        <h2>Unified control plane, flexible execution layer.</h2>
        <p>
          Gameye keeps orchestration concerns separate from your game binaries so teams can iterate on gameplay while
          the platform handles infrastructure placement, scaling, and health workflows.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img
        src="https://gameye.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/gameye_architecture_white.png"
        alt="Gameye platform architecture"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container quick-links">
      <a href="/comparison/">Compare with alternatives</a>
      <a href="/pricing/">Estimate infrastructure cost</a>
      <a href="/docs/">Read technical docs</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingPageLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero .lead {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    max-width: 66ch;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .actions {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .card {
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--gy-color-dark-blue) 12%, #fff);
    background: var(--gy-color-white);
    border-radius: var(--gy-radius-lg);
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .split p {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
  }

  .split img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--gy-radius-lg);
    background: var(--gy-color-bg-alt);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .quick-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .quick-links a {
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--gy-color-dark-blue) 16%, #fff);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.95rem;
    color: var(--gy-color-alt-dark-blue);
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .cards,
    .split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
